This paper deals with the problem of preserving privacy in sequential data, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves generating data that maintains patterns and characteristics of the source data, which is a task that falls under the categories of data management and machine learning (cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in various fields, which could be relevant to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
